The paper introduces a new algorithmic tool for planar graphs, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) or computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. The paper also presents applications related to graph theory and combinatorics, such as Schnyder's realizer theorem and compact encoding of planar graphs, which suggest that it could also belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), or computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
